The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Balasore Alloys Ltd has reported a 302 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 2.46 crore against Rs 61.20 lakh in the year-ago period. Operating profits rose 109% to Rs 8.03 crore from Rs 3.85 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year. EPS jumped 207% to Re 0.43 compared with Re. 0.14 in the year-ago period.

 IFGL Refractories Limited has recorded a 41 per cent rise in profit after tax to Rs 26.24 crore on a consolidated basis for the year ended March 31 2007. Total income rose 40 per cent to Rs 323.89 crore. Earnings per share was higher at Rs 7.58 for 2006-07 against Rs 5.37 in the previous year. 

 Blue Star has posted a 46% growth in net profit at Rs 71.18 crore. Total income grew 36 per cent to Rs 1,607 crore. EPS increased to Rs 7.91 from Rs 5.44. The board of directors has recommended a dividend of Rs 0.60 per share, over and above the interim dividend of Rs 2.40 paid in March 2007.

 S. Kumars Nationwide Ltd has reported a 38.19 per cent increase in turnover at Rs 1,2229.54 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2007. Sales rose 49.9 per cent to Rs 371.66 crore .

 The Royal Classic group plans to set up 63 outlets in the south, taking its total stores to 100. Karnataka will have 30 and the rest will come up in Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu and Kerala.

